DataSelectionSet
public class BaseSelectionSet
extends Object
implements SelectionSet

This implementation of SelectionSet uses a java.util.TreeSet to store the ObjectIDs.

BaseSelectionSet

public BaseSelectionSet(Selectable selectable,
                        Cursor cursor)
Constructs a SelectionSet for the given Selectable, and populates it with DataIds obtained from the Cursor. The Cursor must contain Identifiable Data, otherwise a ClassCastException will be thrown. The Cursor will be dispose'd within this constructor, after it has been used.

Parameters:
selectable - the Selectable
cursor - the cursor
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if selectable or cursor is null
